					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5159298#post-3700109</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5159298/scp-3124#post-3700109</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 04 Feb 2018 03:28:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Communism will win</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>617958</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That was in the first draft, yeah, but it ultimately made the containment procedures way too difficult and it ended up distracting from the rest of the piece.</p> <p>Plus I'm pretty sure there's already multiple SCPs that involve things being visible regardless of obstructions.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5159298#post-3700084</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5159298/scp-3124#post-3700084</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 04 Feb 2018 03:00:58 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3122708</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The fact that it can be seen through liquid and gas is hilarious to me, and makes me wish it could also be seen through solids. Just imagine trying to contain an object that you can see no matter <em>what</em> &#8212; even if your eyes are closed.</p> <p>That being said, yeah this was weird-as-heck and fun.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
